  "text": "Class I HLA-A, B, or C CD8+ T-cytotoxic cells directed against insulin peptides expressed on MHC Class I have been described both in the NOD mouse and in man [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Remarkably, the two NOD mouse epitopes InsB15-23 and InsB25-C34, respectively, bind either very weakly or very strongly to the restriction element, H2-K d [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . The preproinsulin epitopes to several HLA-A/B alleles (including the most frequent allele in the Caucasian population, -A2) (",
